InventoryID: Hillsborough, Mrs. R. A. Hearst coll. 23, ex San Simeon 5434
Bibliographic References: PAdd, no. A 25; I. K. Raubitschek, The Hearst Hillsborough Vases, pp. 81Non Sepcified5, no. 23 (ill.).
Imagery Description: Draped woman holding mirror, nude youth (Dionysos) with thyrsus in right hand, egg in left, and drapery over both arms standing in front of seated Eros, holding phiale and fillet in left hand, fillet in right. Below the handles: female heads.
